article.headline: Evansville 82, Oakland City 42
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- Kenneth Harris scored 21 points to help Evansville cruise past Oakland City 82-42 on Saturday night in the season opener for both teams. Jordan Jahr and Ned Cox each scored 11 points for the Aces while Kavon Lacey helped out with 11 assists. Evansville shot 67 percent from the floor and 58 percent from the free-throw line. The Division II Mighty Oaks got off to a slow start, scoring just 15 points in the first half. But they were competitive in the second half and were outscored just 35-27 in the period. Jeremiah Mitchell led Oakland City with 13 points while Mitch Stahl added 10 points and Eric Head 9.
